1
00:00:01,694 --> 00:00:13,366
Radeon Voice Skill Foundry turns a private spoken operating procedure and a real action demonstration into a reusable, governed Agent Skill.

2
00:00:13,366 --> 00:00:26,150
The public interface runs on Cloudflare, while speech recognition and skill compilation run locally on an AMD Radeon Pro W7900 with ROCm 7.2.1.

3
00:00:29,152 --> 00:00:34,663
I provide the SOP, then perform the six required actions.

4
00:00:34,663 --> 00:00:52,848
Each action is accepted and stored by the server before the interface advances: open the review, filter critical findings, confirm the responsible commitment, prepare drafts, create tentative holds, and export the redacted report.

5
00:00:52,848 --> 00:00:57,256
No irreversible mail or calendar action is executed.

6
00:01:17,153 --> 00:01:25,295
The server sends the original evidence to Qwen3-ASR and Qwen3 on the W7900.

7
00:01:25,295 --> 00:01:37,820
The compiler converts intent and action trace into typed constraints, allowed capabilities, denied capabilities, tests, policy, and a GAIA-compatible `SKILL.md`.

8
00:01:37,820 --> 00:01:43,457
The original transcript hash remains bound to the result.

9
00:01:53,155 --> 00:01:58,066
Sandbox Replay v1 now exercises the generated contract.

10
00:01:58,066 --> 00:02:05,432
Positive fixtures must complete the workflow, while adversarial fixtures attempt unsafe behavior.

11
00:02:05,432 --> 00:02:13,413
`mail.send` stays denied, sensitive values remain redacted, and the report uses approved aliases.

12
00:02:13,413 --> 00:02:20,779
The verifier packages receipts and artifact hashes into a reproducible proof bundle.

13
00:02:31,157 --> 00:02:38,022
Before promotion, the product compares this candidate with the currently promoted skill.

14
00:02:38,022 --> 00:02:44,315
It surfaces permission changes, runtime compatibility, proof status, and workflow impact.

15
00:02:44,315 --> 00:02:52,325
Promotion is an explicit proof-bound governance decision, not an automatic side effect of generation.

16
00:03:07,160 --> 00:03:11,782
The promoted decision appears in the Governance Audit Ledger.

17
00:03:11,782 --> 00:03:18,457
Every event has a monotonic sequence, previous hash, payload hash, and entry hash.

18
00:03:18,457 --> 00:03:24,619
The ledger reconciles its events with the receipts embedded in procedural memory.

19
00:03:24,619 --> 00:03:30,781
Mutation or deletion makes the ledger invalid and blocks further governance actions.

20
00:03:30,781 --> 00:03:34,376
The complete chain is exportable as JSONL.

21
00:03:45,162 --> 00:03:58,746
When the same intent returns, the foundry resolves the identical promoted skill, preserves its action contract, and records exact reuse evidence instead of replanning from scratch.

22
00:03:58,746 --> 00:04:05,538
Changed intent does not take this shortcut; it must compile and verify again.

23
00:04:15,163 --> 00:04:36,379
The final path is voice, server-authoritative demonstration, Radeon inference, least-privilege policy, adversarial proof, impact-aware promotion, tamper-evident governance, and exact reuse, delivered through one stable public product.

24
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:48,300
Terminology boundary: SKILL.md is portable Agent Skill Markdown; no external GAIA conformance is claimed. "Proof-bound" means checked against the current SHA-256 proof hash. Ledger integrity is hash-chained, not digitally signed or externally anchored.
